## Functional form {.smaller}

- Model specification: $y=ax+b$
- Fit the model: estimate free parameters $a$ and $b$ 
- Fitted model: $y=0.39x+2.02$


::: {.cell}
::: {.cell-output-display}
![](model-specification_files/figure-revealjs/unnamed-chunk-10-1.png){width=960}
:::
:::


## Functional form {.smaller}

- high school algebra: $y=ax+b$
- machine learning: $y = w_0 + w_1x_1 + w_2x_2 + ... + w_nx_n$ 
- statistics: $y = β_0 + β_1x_1 + β_2x_2 + ... + β_nx_n + ε$
- matrix: $y = Xβ + ε$


::: {.cell}
::: {.cell-output-display}
![](model-specification_files/figure-revealjs/unnamed-chunk-11-1.png){width=960}
:::
:::




## Model terms {.smaller}

Model terms describe *how* to include our explanatory variables in our model formula — there is more than one way!

1. Intercept
2. Main 
3. Interaction 
4. Transformation

## Intercept  {.smaller}

  - in R: `y ~ 1`
  - in eq: $y=\beta_0 + \varepsilon$


::: {.cell}
::: {.cell-output-display}
![](model-specification_files/figure-revealjs/unnamed-chunk-12-1.png){width=960}
:::
:::


## Main {.smaller}

  - in R: `y ~ 1 + year + gender` 
  - in eq: $y = \beta_0 + \beta_1x_1 + \beta_2x_2$

::: {.panel-tabset}

## year 


